data.description: Step into the past and embrace the timeless charm of this historic beauty, nestled in the heart of Minot's Eastwood Park, among other cherished historic homes. This gem boasts four bedrooms, two bathrooms, and a one-stall tucked-under garage, all framed by a picturesque white picket fence. With over 1400 square feet of spacious living area above ground, this home seamlessly marries space and cozy comfort.  The well-appointed kitchen features white cabinetry, generous countertop space, and modern stainless steel appliances. Your dining room, perfect for hosting gatherings, opens onto a convenient back porch – ideal for those who relish barbecues and entertaining.  On the main floor, discover a versatile bedroom or office with easy access to a three-quarter bathroom. Unwind in the generous living room, your sanctuary after a long day of work or play.  Upstairs, you'll find three additional bedrooms and a full bathroom, offering ample space for your family's needs. The basement remains a blank canvas, ready to fulfill your storage requirements.  Outdoors, the sizable front yard is fenced and adorned with mature trees, offering a serene atmosphere. The back of the property provides off-street parking and a practical storage shed.  For over a century, this home has been cherished and adored, and now, it awaits you to become the next custodian of its rich history. Reach out to your favorite Realtor® to arrange your private tour and secure your place in this enduring piece of Minot's heritage.
